@jonathan-hurley, I'm not against the generic solution (that was my original suggestion), but it seems to be a big change in 2.7.

> Also - shouldn't this also happen when the DataNode is removed as a component, but the host remains?

For some reason the customer who asked this only want it after host deletion.

@swagle @AaronWjf We had to remove this cleanup step since there were other components relying on AMS HBase Zk connections like HWX SmartSense. 

However, I restart AMS in embedded mode regularly and don't see it failing. There are a few call exceptions to HBase but it starts up fine. 

What is the need to do this? Do you see any consistent failure during restart?
